# ── Large generated datasets (regeneratable with phase_2_generate.py) ─────────
# Commit:   data/grounding/unicode_verification.csv  (small, proves rule works)
#           data/datasets/*/split_stats.json          (small reference stats)
#           src/backend/generation/examples.json      (generated once, expensive)
#           data/datasets/*/raw/generated_raw.csv    (large, need to be portable, local->kaggle->local)
# Ignore:   everything else in data/datasets/

data/datasets/*/raw/checkpoint.csv
data/datasets/*/train.csv
data/datasets/*/val.csv
data/datasets/*/test.csv

# ── Trained model artifacts (large, regeneratable with phase_5/6) ─────────────
# Commit:   experiments/*/classical/results/         (metrics CSVs, small)
#           experiments/*/transformers/results/       (metrics CSVs, small)
#           experiments/*/eda_plots/                  (useful PNG plots)
#           experiments/*/eda_summary.json            (small stats)
# Ignore:   model pickles and checkpoint weights

experiments/*/classical/models/
experiments/*/transformers/models/

# ── MLflow ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# MLflow stores artifacts and metrics locally. Use `mlflow ui` to view.
# Don't commit — can be regenerated by re-running training phases.
mlruns/

# ── Jupyter ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.ipynb_checkpoints/
*.ipynb

